quoteFirst: All the ladies, talking together, said it was really miraculous how she thought of such lovely metaphors.  And it brought the idea home to one so beautifully—a lily swaying in the breeze! Personally, we recalled that the last time we saw anyone trying to walk like a lily swaying in the breeze, was about
quoteLast: on a down-town thoroughfare.  The person in question was trying to carry a most splendiferous slosh past a watchful guardian of the law without affording an excuse for police intervention.  The result was something like a lily, and also something like a wrecking-crane that had got out of control.
